                <mxCell id="TITLE-1" value="Graph Autoencoder — NetFlow Anomaly Detection" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontStyle=1;fontSize=18;fontFamily=Segoe UI;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="170" y="40" width="520" height="30" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="PLAIN-1" value="&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;How it works&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;1.&amp;nbsp; Turn network traffic into a &lt;b&gt;graph&lt;/b&gt;: IP addr = nodes, netflow features = edges.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;2.&amp;nbsp; Learn a &lt;b&gt;&#39;fingerprint&#39;&lt;/b&gt; for every IP, using largely &lt;b&gt;normal &lt;/b&gt;traffic.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;3.&amp;nbsp; Try to &lt;b&gt;reconstruct&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;each flow using only those fingerprints.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;4.&amp;nbsp; Rebuilt badly = &lt;b&gt;anomalous&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;→ flag it as a possible attack.&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFF2CC;strokeColor=#D6B656;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=10;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Segoe UI;gradientColor=none;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="37.5" y="805" width="378.5" height="176" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
